  "body": "### Description\n\n@IfBuildProperty does not allow multiple property names to be checked on the optional beans- similar to spring - @ConditionalOnProperty\r\n\r\n- \n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nShould able to declare like the below - \r\n\r\n`@IfBuildProperty( { name = \"kafka.test.flag1\", stringValue = \"true\"},\r\n{ name = \"kafka.test.flag2\", stringValue = \"false\"},\r\n{ name = \"kafka.test.flag3\", stringValue = \"true\"})` \r\nAll value checks are OR based - (can be considered AND based - depending on the implementation - and easiness of usage.)  \r\n\r\nIn the AND case (Can be considered OR - depending on the implementation - and easiness of usage)-> defining multiple times the same annotation -\r\n```\r\n@IfBuildProperty( name = \"kafka.test.flag1\", stringValue = \"true\")\r\n@IfBuildProperty( name = \"kafka.test.flag2\", stringValue = \"false\")\r\n@IfBuildProperty( name = \"kafka.test.flag3\", stringValue = \"false\")\r\n```\r\nplease check if this is feasible. ",
